Health Minister Zweli Mkhize is in the Eastern Cape - checking COVID19 ready facilities and meeting with the provincial command structures to get an update on how the province is dealing with the continued spread of the pandemic.  EAST LONDON - Health Minister Zweli Mkhize is checking COVID-19 ready facilities in the Eastern Cape. Mkhize will also meet with the provincial command structures to get an update on how the province is dealing with the continued spread of the pandemic. The minister is joined by Eastern Cape Health MEC Sindiswa Gomba. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8 am to 4 pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.